==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Proven
<hw>Prov"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>p. p. ⟦or⟧ a.</pos>
<def>Proved.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Accusations firmly <xex>proven</xex> in his
mind.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of this which was the principal charge, and was generally believed
to be<qex>proven</qex>, he was acquitted.</q> <rj><qau>Jowett (Thucyd.
).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Not proven</b></col> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld>, <cd>a
verdict of a jury that the guilt of the accused is not made out, though
not disproved.</cd> <rj><au>Mozley & W.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Provenance</ent>⟦br⟧
